name: Anderson Cooper
summary: New Year's Eve festivities will be graced by the return of CNN's "New Year's Eve Live With Anderson Cooper & Andy Cohen." The beloved duo will host the show, which will feature a lineup of special guests. Tune in to watch the festivities live on December 31st at 8 pm EST. Co-host Andy Cohen, known for his tequila-infused celebrations, plans to bring his signature drink to the show, leaving Anderson Cooper gasping for air after a second shot. Cohen has revealed that the most annoying aspect of co-hosting with Cooper is having to accommodate his early bedtimes, forcing Cohen to tone down his revelry. Cooper has also shared his views on their partnership, expressing surprise at Cohen's energetic dancing despite his age. Viewers can catch the show on CNN, or stream it online via CNN.com, the CNN app, or on-demand services such as Hulu Live TV, YouTube TV, and fuboTV.

name: Puerto Rico
summary: Puerto Rico has experienced a widespread power outage that began on New Year's Eve, leaving nearly the entire island without electricity. The outage began at around 9:00 PM EST and affected over 1 million customers. As of the latest reports, power has been slowly restored to some areas, but many remain in darkness. The cause of the outage is still under investigation, but there are reports that it may have been caused by an explosion at a power plant. Officials are working to restore power as quickly as possible, but it is unclear when full service will be restored.
